[[File:Gesina ter Borch selfportrait.jpg|thumb|Self portrait]]
'''Gesina ter Borch''' (1633&ndash;1690) was a [[Dutch Golden Age]] painter, whose work mostly consists of watercolour paintings in albums.
==Biography==
[[File:Gesina ter Borch - echtelijke ruzie.jpg|thumb|left|Domestic fight]]
[[File:Borch, Gerard Ter II and Borch, Gesina - Memorial Portrait of Moses ter Borch - 1667-69.jpg|thumb|right|Posthumous portrait of her brother Moses, painted by Gesina with help from her brother Gerard, ca. 1667-1669]]
Gesina ter Borch was born in [[Deventer]].  According to the RKD she was the daughter of [[Gerard ter Borch the Elder]] and the sister of [[Gerard ter Borch]], who taught her to draw and paint, and who painted her and other members of the family several times.<ref name=RKD>[http://www.rkd.nl/rkddb/dispatcher.aspx?action=search&database=ChoiceArtists&search=priref=10683 Gesina ter Borch] in the [[RKD]]</ref>
She lived her whole life on the Sassenstraat in Zwolle, where she died.<ref>[http://www.historici.nl/Onderzoek/Projecten/DVN/lemmata/data/Borch Gesina ter Borch] at [[Historici.nl]]</ref>
